(AP Photo/Eric Gay) Alabama 's Eddie Jackson (4) runs past Texas A&M quarterback Kyle Allen (10) as he returns an interception for a touchdown during the first half of an NCAA college football game, Saturday, Oct. 17, 2015, in ... more Photo: Eric Gay, STF / Associated Press No contest — again: Tide rolls Aggies 1 / 1 Back to Gallery COLLEGE STATION — Texas A&M’s two quarterbacks had enjoyed plenty of praise this season. One for leading the Aggies to a 5-0 start and a top 10 ranking, the other for his triumphs the past three years as a Texas high school football legend.
But sophomore starter Kyle Allen threw three interceptions and freshman Kyler Murray added another in limited action, and the Aggies were left with a handful of questions at the position following No. 10 Alabama’s 41-23 victory over No. 9 A&M on Saturday at Kyle Field.
